    {
      "id": "ef2b593b-fe70-4b06-aff5-f6312b219ce8",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Recent years have seen the proliferation of Deep Learning to address Knowledge Tracing problems. However, these tend to oversimplify exercise records into knowledge sequences which leaves behind the importance of individual questions. Moreover, the models focus on question-right vs question wrong and don’t tend to worry whether the learner actually knows the concepts involved in the question. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "ef2b593b-fe70-4b06-aff5-f6312b219ce8",
        "parent": {
          "type": "page_id",
          "page_id": "d4dbe55d-5d93-4ed6-b8b4-1c318d6b003a"
        },
        "created_time": "2024-08-06T16:18:00.000Z",
        "last_edited_time": "2025-08-10T22:41:00.000Z",
        "created_by": {
          "object": "user",
          "id": "20a7795c-3622-4527-bd13-5ddbf48dc31d"
        },
        "last_edited_by": {
